From Chris Harris, Yreka Union Elementary School District Superintendent:

We recognize you are anxious to hear our plans for next year. Gov Newsom announced guidelines today and we will review those and adjust our reopening plan accordingly. We will have a distance learning option available and then we are developing plans for on campus and/or a hybrid model. In the meantime, feel free to contact Mr. Harris at 842-1168 or charris@yrekausd.net if you have questions. A parent survey will be out next week to gather your input and opinions. Thank you!

post_text:
Based on the recommendation of the Siskiyou County Superintendent of Schools, State, and Federal officials, Yreka Union school sites will continue to be closed to students through the end of the school year.

While the school buildings may be closed, school is still in session. Teachers will continue to support students through distance learning. If your student is struggling, please contact your teacher via email. More information will be coming from your schools on how the school work will be deployed through the end of the year. We will continue to provide food service as well.

We will continue to evaluate end of year activities such as graduation and measurement of students' achievement toward grade level standards. Our staff has been exemplary during this time and you can expect that they will continue their great work.

This is not the most positive way to end our year. We greatly appreciate your continued support and patience. Our staff will continue to rise above and provide for your student. We all need to work together to keep our connections.

Siskiyou County Probation
December 11, 2019 at 9:20 PM ·

Tonight 41 youth that were selected to shop for themselves and their family for Christmas spent time with several of our officers at the Shop with a Cop event at Walmart. All Siskiyou County Law Enforcement were represented tonight as well.

A big thank you to Sgt. Ray Boutin from The Yreka Police Department, who has spent several hours on this event. He was very instrumental in the planning, and solicited support from several community partners, including Walmart, Round Table Pizza and the Siskiyou Central Credit Union.

This event not only gives these youth the opportunity to spread Christmas cheer, but all of the officers have the honor to bring joy to the families who will benefit from this.
